I have a AMD 486DX2-80 running on a SIS471B chipset (green)
motherboard. It gets:

	Norton SI		~173
	PcBench 9 CpuMark 16	~100

This VLB motherboard has 256K external cache and 16MB of 60ns
memory. All BIOS wait states, memory speed settings, etc are
set to their fastest possible settings and it is absolutely
stable. These benchmarks demonstrate that motherboard chip-set
has a substantial impact on overall performance. You can't
go by just CPU clock speed alone.

