That's not too unusual.  After all, it's 2x40.  Not sure why
you use ~100 (maybe 99 or 95?) since the result is a single
number.  Fast DX2/66s pull 85 or so (typically 77 or so).  The
advantage of a 2*40 is the memory speed -- happens at 40MHz.
Even a DX4/100 writes only at 33MHz and so if it the benchmark
were only, say, 1 million writes to memory, the DX2/80 would
beat the DX4/100.  But, yes, chipset and motherboard do matter,
so does memory, video, disk, and everything else, often even
more.
